{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-tsx","path":"/2014/11/07/interactive-light-sculptures/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"siteUrl":"https://blog.aboutme.be"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"6fe6ed3f-5d5f-507f-b267-b2383076c9dd","excerpt":"A couple of weeks back, my Happy-Banana partner in crime Koen and I were approached by artist Tom Dekyvere for an interactive sculpture project. He wanted to…","html":"<p>A couple of weeks back, my Happy-Banana partner in crime Koen and I were approached by artist <a href=\"http://tomandliendekyvere.com/\">Tom Dekyvere</a> for an interactive sculpture project.</p>\n<p>He wanted to put interactive artworks at the Catch festival in Utrecht and was looking for a partner to help build the electronics. The sculptures needed to respond with light and sound on the people around. Challenge accepted!</p>\n<p>We started experimenting with different libraries and electronics, and quickly settled on the <a href=\"https://sensorium.github.io/Mozzi/\">Mozzi library</a> for Arduino Sound synthesis on the software side, together with a maxbotix ultrasonic distance sensor, mosfet and some 12V ledstrips. Our first experiments were promising:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\" style=\"padding-bottom: 56.25%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden; margin-bottom: 1.0725rem\" > <iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/432268662\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; fullscreen\" allowfullscreen style=\" position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; \"></iframe> </div>\n<p>The next step was replicating this 6 times, which proved to take more time than we thought. We finished soldering the final board just when Tom was here to pick up our hardware!</p>\n<p>Here’s a clip where you can see Tom’s sculptures lighting up and reacting to the audience:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-resp-iframe-wrapper\" style=\"padding-bottom: 42.5%; position: relative; height: 0; overflow: hidden; margin-bottom: 1.0725rem\" > <iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/432275416\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; fullscreen\" allowfullscreen style=\" position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%; \"></iframe> </div>","fields":{"slug":"/2014/11/07/interactive-light-sculptures/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Interactive Light Sculptures","date":"07 Nov, 2014","description":false,"tags":["arduino","sound","sculptures","interactive"],"hasCover":true,"cover":{"publicURL":"/static/6c840fc0e5356653145f910afce9bed5/preview.jpg","childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"tracedSVG":"data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg%20xmlns='http://www.w3.org/2000/svg'%20width='62'%20height='62'%20viewBox='0%200%2062%2062'%20preserveAspectRatio='none'%3e%3cpath%20d='M0%2017v17h4c4%200%205%201%206%207l1%204-4-1-5-2c-1-3-2%200-2%2010v10h60v-6c0-8%202-9%202-1l1-24-1-25v7c0%202-9%201-11%200s-2-3-2-7V0H0v17m32%205c-3%200-12%2010-11%2012l-1%201c-2%200-1%205%201%207l2%201%203%201%206%201%206%201h2l1-2c1%201%203%200%204-2%202-5%202-7-1-11-2-2-4-4-4-6-1-2-5-4-8-3'%20fill='%23d3d3d3'%20fill-rule='evenodd'/%3e%3c/svg%3e","aspectRatio":0.7493606138107417,"src":"/static/6c840fc0e5356653145f910afce9bed5/d6678/preview.jpg","srcSet":"/static/6c840fc0e5356653145f910afce9bed5/40917/preview.jpg 293w,\n/static/6c840fc0e5356653145f910afce9bed5/3c0b6/preview.jpg 585w,\n/static/6c840fc0e5356653145f910afce9bed5/d6678/preview.jpg 690w","srcWebp":"/static/6c840fc0e5356653145f910afce9bed5/f3dc3/preview.webp","srcSetWebp":"/static/6c840fc0e5356653145f910afce9bed5/05ceb/preview.webp 293w,\n/static/6c840fc0e5356653145f910afce9bed5/5c538/preview.webp 585w,\n/static/6c840fc0e5356653145f910afce9bed5/f3dc3/preview.webp 690w","sizes":"(max-width: 690px) 100vw, 690px"}}}}},"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"fields":{"slug":"/2018/10/10/quick-hack-timing-air-pump-with-arduino/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Quick Hack, Timing an Air Pump with Arduino","tags":["arduino","installation"],"cover":{"publicURL":"/static/77b06fcf3f099b0cb43897e9e3